OL,3,CFormer Wales winger Leighton James
OL,4,Cdies aged 71
OL,6,FOriginally from the Gorseinon area of
OL,7,FSwansea, James was born in 1953. He
OL,8,Fwould go on to represent his hometown
OL,9,Fclub, the Swans, on 98 occasions, with
OL,10,F27 goals under his belt.
OL,12,FHe went on to play with Bury, Newport
OL,13,FCounty, and Burnley again before
OL,14,Fhanging up his boots professionally
OL,15,Fand moving into management roles.
OL,17,FHe also took on pundit work for the
OL,18,FBBC and was a columnist.
